<span id="freeTextContainer13540674467631616235">I had a great time reading this collection of &quot;love gone wrong&quot; stories. I even came up with my own alternate titles for them. (Beware: Spoilers Ahead!) &quot;I love her, but she loves someone else.&quot; &quot;I love my dog, but the lady I work for wants me to kill it.&quot; &quot;I love her, but I was too shy to tell her and now she&apos;s gone.&quot; &quot;I love her, but she thinks I&apos;m a child and had an affair with my dad instead.&quot; &quot;Imagine if King Lear was a minor nobleman in Tsarist Russia.&quot; &quot;I love my wife, but she&apos;s having er</span>
  <span id="freeText13540674467631616235" style="display:none">I had a great time reading this collection of "love gone wrong" stories. I even came up with my own alternate titles for them. (Beware: Spoilers Ahead!) "I love her, but she loves someone else." "I love my dog, but the lady I work for wants me to kill it." "I love her, but I was too shy to tell her and now she's gone." "I love her, but she thinks I'm a child and had an affair with my dad instead." "Imagine if King Lear was a minor nobleman in Tsarist Russia." "I love my wife, but she's having erotic dreams about my best friend." </span>
